{
  "text": "A bipartite network projection [CITATION_1] is carried out to discover the relationship between the topics identified. The projection relates topics that are common to documents, and the number of documents in common giving the weight between topics, giving a measure of how strong their relationship is. Then, the weights are min-max scaled between 0 and 1. A distance measure d ij between topics i and j can be written as the complement of the scaled weights:",
